      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PENNY'S LEGACY (8) is racing well without winning, recording three minors on end, the latest hitting the ground running with a fast early sectional but finishing in the minors again when third (24.21) over 425m at Bendigo. Well-placed to take this out. DIVA'S ROSE (2) produced a modest effort most recently when sixth at Mt Gambier over 400m behind Poke Salad Annie (23.78) in a Grade 6. In the mix. GOLD STRIPES (7) struggled to get involved last start after being shuffled back early at this track, but prior to that won easily by 5.5 lengths at this track (22.62) beating Saint Xavier in a Grade 4/5 on March 23. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings four times from seven attempts. A big run wouldn't surprise. TINKER DOT (4) is a last start all-the-way winner. Sure to figure prominently.",
